commit.message:
Avoid AVX3 ternary instructions under MSAN

MemorySanitizer interprets these as branching, which is typically not desirable
as Highway code may be operating on uninitialized padding data. Instead, use
bitwise instructions when built with MemorySanitizer.

This doesn't address IfVecThenElse, which has some inexplicable and undebugged
behavior when implemented with IfThenElse(MaskFromVec(mask), ...).
